  	 		<h4>Week 22</h4>
  	 		<p><b>Baby : </b>the brain's intensive growth slows down. brain has enough neurones now to last for the entire life. the baby's brain is about hundred grams and there are grooves and wrinkles in it. the babies curious and now investigates is feelings and tactile sensations. The baby now touches his face, body, umbilical cord and starts making faces, stretches its legs up to the face and occasionally taps on the uterine wall. The movements are becoming more willful and complex. </p>
  	 		<p>The babies skeletal system and bones now strengthen.  The baby's body proportion is  changing now. The arms and legs of the foetus are growing at a greater speed as compared to the head. The heart is also growing. It now pumps up to 30 litres a day. </p>
  	 		<p>the liver is also able to separate the toxins and expel them across the placenta. The uterus is now roomyvand the baby is able to twist, dance, turn and flip flop in the uterus. Ok now really count on the frequencies of his moments.</p>
  	 		<p>The sense of sight is also becoming more fine-tuned. The foetus can  now perceive light and dark much better than before, even with those fused eyelids.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Mother : </b>22 weeks is a great time to enjoy pregnancy. You can feel your baby wing around which will provide you a sense of joy, tranquility and optimism. Your baby is getting pretty big nowadays but don't worry it won't be that uncomfortable. but your tummy is not the only thing that's growing these days have you looked down at your feet quick look now before you can't see them anymore if you are like many expected women you will discover that feat gets bigger too.</p>
  	 		<p>While some foot growth can be attributed to pregnancy swelling, there's another reason that feet increases in size during pregnancy and sometimes don't shrink back afterward. Remember relaxin, that pregnancy hormones that loosens ligament and joints around your pelvis so your baby can fit through ? well it doesn't discriminate between the ligaments  you would want lossened up,  like those pelvic ones, and those you would rather just leave alone, like the ones in your feet.</p>
  	 		<p>your weight is gradually increasing week by week average weight gain will be approximately 5 to 7 kgs. You may start feeling Braxton Hicks contractions now, these are the practice contractions which uterus practices since conception but you may start feeling them now, they are irregular in their nature.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Tips</b></p>
  	 		<p><b>Braxton Hicks contractions : </b>Is here you transparencing for delivery? if you feel irregular, painless ,squeezing sensations in your abdomen. it is  Braxton Hicks contractions and are not dangerous. they are bit like a dress rehearsal. Keep in mind that while they can be hard to distinguish from the real thing they are not efficient enough to push your baby out the way.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Magnesium supplement : </b>In addition to strengthening babies bones and teeth, magnesium works to stimulate enzyme function, regulate insulin and control blood sugar levels. If you are deficient in magnesium you may feel fatigued and lack muscle strength or have like cramps or restless legs. other severe consequences can include poor fetal growth or pre eclampsia. Ask your doctor if you should add a magnation supplement to your diet.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Fit in work : </b>Scientific research shows that you are not only the one who benefits from pregnancy exercise apparently babies of mom's who exercise throughout pregnancy score higher on average and general intelligence test by age 4. Not only will your workout boost your muscle power,but it will also boost your baby's brain power!</p>
  	 		<p><b>Take breath : </b>now's a great time to learn some soothing relaxation exercise not just because they can help you cope with pregnancy worries but because they will come in handy in your life as a new mom.  Yoga is a fabulous distressor, but here is a technique you can use just about anywhere, anytime to soothe your soul. Sit with your eyes closed and imagine a beautiful peaceful scene (maybe a sunset over your favourite beach  or serene mountain ) then working your way up from your toes to your face, concentrate on relaxing every muscle of your body. Slowly and  deeply breathe only through your nose and choose a simple word to repeat a loud every time you exhale. 10 minutes should do the trick. Doing even a minute or two is better than nothing.</p>

  	 	<div id="w3">
      </div>

  	 		<h4>Week 23 </h4>
  	 		<p><b>Baby : </b>Your baby is around 11 inches long and just 500 to 700 grams in weight, for baby should double his weight over the next four weeks alone and you may feel as though you do, too. His skin is bit wrinkled since it grows a lot faster than fat but soon he will start to fit his frame as fat deposits fill the things out. And although at 23 weeks pregnant your baby's organs and bones are visible through the skin will become less transparent once those fat deposits settle in.</p>
  	 		<p>You have probably heard your developing baby's heartbeat through a Doppler and number of times already, though you never get tired of hearing it, but by now you or your doctor might also be able to hear it through a standard stethoscope. what a hearttrob!</p>
  	 		<p>the lungs are not yet ready to breathe outside the womb but they are developing  at  fast pace. The baby completes an action of 60 breaths per minute inside the womb. The lung maturity and structural development is running at a greatest speed because the circulatory system is now dwelling inside the lungs and giving proper blood supply till the alveoli down there. The alveoli's structural development starts to get complete and it starts secreting some amount of surfactant. Surfactant is a soapy substance secreted by alveolar cells that is a must for lungs to breath. Without surfactant any one of us individual wont be  able to survive. </p>
  	 		<p>scientists believe that at 23 weeks of pregnancy, the baby starts to dream because it develops in REM sleep. In this sleep the baby opens eyes or becomes awake for few seconds in one hour and then goes back to sleep again.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Mother : </b>The baby's brain is developing now and the oxygen is ultimate supply for its brains development. To ensure the good development of your fetal brain you must have an hour or so of gentle walk in open air. </p>
  	 		<p>So try talking to your baby as much as possible because the baby will start recognising your voice and voices of the people around you. You may feel a sharp kick or active moment if there is a sudden loud noise. Avoid listening to harsh, rock and fast track sounds.</p>
  	 		<p>Babies immune system is aggressively working now. The baby is almost never exposed to bacterias and viruses from others blood because it is protected by a unit known as placenta which filters the harmful toxins and organisms and never allows baby to get infected but there are chances that if the infection is serious the baby might get infected. So it is very necessary for a mother to prevent her from any communicable diseases during her pregnancy as much as possible.</p>
  	 		<p>At 23 weeks pregnant your mind is fussy and your feet are growing. The palms of your hands and soles of your feet might be red and you might be more prone to heat rash and skin tags. stretch marks are blooming in vibrant shades of pink, red,  purple, redish brown or dark brown on pretty much every available surface of skin and wait what's that dark line running down the center of your belly? it's called Linea nigra a common emblem of pregnancy that maybe more noticeable in dark skin women. The linea nigra runs between your belly button and your pubic area. It's caused by the same pregnancy hormones responsible for all the skin discolorations you might be seeing like the darker shades of your areola and deeper tone of the freckles on your arms and legs.  Some women  usually those with darker skin notice discoloration on face too especially in the area around the nose, forehead, cheeks and eyes. It's called the mask of pregnancy because it appears as a mask line configuration on the face.</p>
  	 		<p>All this skin changes will fade within a few months after delivery. In the mean time bring on the concealer do not use the bleaching creams which would work anyway.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Tips</b></p>
  	 		<p><b>Oral hygiene</b></p>
  	 		<p>It is wrongly said that a mother loses its calcium because the baby utilizes the calcium from mothers teeth and cause dental caries the actual reason behind increased dental caries during pregnancy is hormonal shift, vomiting, nausea, morning sickness and poor oral hygiene. Morning sickness, dietary changes and vomiting causes pH imbalance in mouth demineralizes  the teeth and causes dental carries. You can take care of your dental cavities by doing twice a daily fluoride toothpaste using floss and mouth wash.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Get proper sleep : </b>It can be almost as hard to get a good night's sleep when you are pregnant as it is when you are new parent. With all that is going on in your body - your brain - its no wonder that a full night's rest can be so elusive. If you find it hard to get comfortable try sliding a pillow between your legs and resting with your knees bent.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Be hydrated : </b>Keep bottle of water by your side at all times. Staying hydrated helps maintain your additional blood volume, renews amniotic fluid and voices milk production. Though it really varies  based on your body type and size, how active you are and so on. The general rule of thumb is somewhere between 8 to 10 glasses of water a day from all sources, but be sure to talk to  your practitioner about what works for you and your situation.</p>
  	 		<p><b>Prevent urinary tract infections : </b>Now that it's being pushed by your growing uterus, your bladder makes the perfect breeding ground for bacteria and that can lead to urinary tract infection. Luckily there's a number of ways you can reduce your chance of developing a UTI during pregnancy. Drink plenty of water and cranberry juice, ideally  that doesn't contain sugar. Check out your urine colour - if it's dark not straw coloured, you are not getting enough fluids and could be setting yourself up for UTI. Don't hold it in pee as soon as you feel the earth and can find a bathroom. Concentrate on completely empting your bladder, when you urinate and try leaning forward when you feel to pee. wipe your front to rear after you use the toilet. Clean your genitals and the area surrounding them particularly after having sex. Wear all cotton undergarments and takes showers rather than baths whenever possible.</p>
  	 	
