			<h4>Week 24</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b>By 24 weeks, the 7th month, the baby is experiencing sleep and wake cycles. For about 6 to 9 hours a day, the baby is really into an active mood. Baby will tilts his head, raises eyebrows and would kick around, would try to feel everything the baby can feel and touch . This helps for his mental development.</p>
			<p>the growth rate of foetus is accelerated as the foetus is producing his own growth hormone.</p>
			<p>development of lung is now at its fullest the alveoli are now whining and are starting to produce the surfactant. This effect is the vital thing to help your baby breathe comfortably when his born right now, the lungs are very immature to breathe on its own. </p>
			<p>The baby Taj making facial expressions like yawning, frowing,  smiling, sucking. the baby will try exercising facial muscles.</p>
			<p>The baby even start responding by sudden jerks to  light or sound and even to mother's emotions.</p>
			<p>the baby skin is still red and little wrinkly. Yhe oil glands and sweat glands has now started developing. a little later subcutaneous layer of fat will accumulated just beneath the skin making it more smoother and more elastic.</p>

			<p><b>Mother : </b>This is the time when a mother will notice sudden shoot in her appetite. Her body will get more than before. your weight increases by 300 to 500 grams every week. Average total weight gain since the start of pregnancy would be 7 kgs. If your weight gain is going ahead, then your doctor adviced to start incorporating some physical exercise that is not harmful to the foetus. Avoid doing lunges, jumps and kicks  but you can do a modest amount of walking and little stretching if that's advisable. overweight causes a problem in the labour so you should try maintaining yourself in the shape as much as possible. Prenatal yoga, fresh air walks and swimming are best for you as of now.</p>
			<p>Your belly button will be pushed outwards because of your enlarging uterus will push anything that is coming in its way. This should get normal after the delivery, though the belly button and the skin of tummy might look a little stretched out but you can take it as a badge of honor that only moms get to wear.</p>
			<p>Carpal tunnel syndrome will be aggravated during pregnancy because in pregnancy there is increased in fluid in your body and this is mostly accumulated in lower extremities during the daytime, when you sleep this fluid is redistributed to other parts of your body especially at the level of wrist which will cause the compression of nerve and may cause tingling and numbness. the best way to avoid it is sleeping with your hands lying over a pillow. If you are doing repeated exercise is like playing piano or typing you should take a little bit of rest from doing so.</p>

			<p><b>Tips</b></p>
			<p><b>glucose screening : </b>Between 24 to 28 weeks of your pregnancy your consultant may advise you to test for glucose screening. It is sometimes known as oral glucose tolerance test, it is done to diagnose whether you have gestational diabetes, a temporary condition related with pregnancy or not. As diabetes have serious harmful effects on foetus, it is better to get screened. You are at increased risk of having gestational diabetes if you are overweight, have more amount of abdominal fat or are having a family history of diabetes.</p>
			<p><b>shower : </b>As you might be suffering from dry skin, it is better to take short showers- with use of lukewarm water, not very hot water or cold water with mild cleanser. You can definitely put any moisture riser after your bath.</p>
			<p><b>eat plenty of proteins : </b>Proteins are made up of amino acids which are building blocks of every cell of your baby's body to make it more adorable and more functional. The brain indeed needs protein for better functioning of your babies walk, talk, smile and various activities. During pregnancy you need at least 3 servings of proteins that is 75 grams of protein everyday. Most of the people achieve this goal but if you are a vegan or vegetarian diet it might be a little difficult for you to reach this. To compensate this you may end up eating one cup full of sprouted beans.</p>
			<p><b>keep a track of weight gain : </b>Ideal weight gain during pregnancy is 9 to 12 KG of your pre pregnancy weight but your doctor will advise you the target of weight gain depending upon your pre pregnancy weight your BMI and your family histories of diabetes and hypertension. By now you should be gaining at least 1 kg a month, if you are not gaining weight then there are chances of preterm delivery or IUGR to your baby. now the doctors will themselves keep a count of your weight gain and would advise you to either increase, maintain or slightly reduce your weight depending upon your obesity and nourishment.</p>

		<div id="w5"> 
    </div>
      
			<h4>Week 25</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b>By the 25th week of pregnancy the baby's face is already formed. The features are more humanly now and with the help of sonography and little imagination you can decide whether the baby looks like mum , dad or grandma or grandpa. The external ears continue to develop.</p>
			<p>The baby's muscles start to develop and each muscle takes its own responsibility for various functions. The reproductive system is now developing in its fullest. In boys the testicles that are formed will start descending from abdomen into scrotum whereas in females the vagina is still completing its process of development.</p>
			<p>Development of baby's bones is now started the baby is getting into a shape of calcified skeleton. Bones are still soft and cartilaginous. this is the time when mother requires  to have proper calcium intake so that it helps in development of baby's skeletal system.</p>
			<p>The bone marrow now starts participating in the blood formation. by now the responsibility of blood formation was on liver and spleen, by 5 weeks of pregnancy the blood formation is carried forward by liver but now slowly the bone marrow will take over the function.</p>
			<p>Baby's skin colour is becoming pink now because of the small blood vessels called capillaries are forming under the skin and filling with blood.By 25 weeks pregnant lungs are still very much works- in -progress. Do they are already beginning to produce surfactant a substance that will help them expand with oxygen after baby is born, the lungs are still too undeveloped to sufficiently send oxygen to the bloodstream and release carbon dioxide when the baby exhales.</p>
			<p>The lungs aren't the only system that's maturing for Air intake. Your baby's nostrils and nose are starting to work this week.This allows your little one to begin taking practice breaths. Baby could also be able to smell various sense in utero by this week too.if not that sense will kick in by the third trimester.</p>

			<p><b>Mother : </b>By 25 weeks pregnant your belly is getting bigger and heavier by each passing week and your baby inside is also growing day by day, second by second and also the baby is becoming very active and will start kicking and you might feel the kicks causing little discomfort and pain the baby will make you feel like you are literally "with your child."</p>
			<p>The pregnancy is associated with some discomforts,  enlarging uterus will press upon the internal organs, may cause gastritis, regurgitation of food, sleeplessness, difficulty in breathing, hemorrhoids, swellings in legs and frequent urination.</p>
			<p>Constipation can aggravate piles so you can prevent it by increasing the intake of fluid and fibre like fruits, vegetables and whole grains. Doing pelvic floor exercises and trying not to strain while defecation can help too.</p>
			<p>Your dental health now onwards is also very important because in pregnancy if there is untreated gingivitis it can progress to serious infections call periodontitis which is linked to premature birth and even increased risk of preeclampsia.</p>

			<p><b>Tips</b></p>
			<p><b>Use moisturizer : </b>because of enlarging uterus the skin over your belly stretches and may become itching there are chances that you may develop stretch marks so it's better to do gentle massage with moisturizer.</p>
			<p><b>note eye symptoms : </b>Your eyes are yet another seemingly random part of your body affected by hormones. During this time your vision might be less and your contact lenses might be less comfortable to wear. Even though your retaining fluid ironically your eyes maybe drier than ever. But don't worry eye symptoms like skin symptoms, will disappear after delivery .Be sure to let your practitioner no was going on so he or she can help you with.</p>
			<p><b>watch your BP : </b>Preeclampsia or arterial hypertension is a condition which may develop in pregnancy because of arterial spasms of the placenta. The clinical signs of it are very important and a lady can diagnose it at home. If she is gaining more wait more than 2 kg weight  in one week or if she's feeling severe pedal edema which pits on pressure or if she is suffering from headache and dizziness, right upper epigastrium pain, blurring of vision. These all are known as warning signs of preeclampsia and a lady should visit hospital at the earliest if any one of them is appreciable. The doctor will check your BP and will do urine test if needed and if this comes to be positive you will be started on some antihypertensive medications which is necessary to take on time and should not be stopped without doctors advice.</p>
